// Objective: Learn to manipulate and interact with strings using various methods.
// 1. Declare a string variable named greeting and assign it the value "Hello, World!".
let greeting = "Hello, World!";
// 2. Use the toUpperCase method to print the greeting in uppercase.
console.log(greeting.toUpperCase());
// 3. Use the replace method to replace "World" with "JavaScript".
let newGreeting = greeting.replace("World", "JavaScript");
// 4. Print the new greeting to the console.
console.log(newGreeting);
// Exercise: Try other string methods like slice(), indexOf(), and includes(). Experiment with different string values and operations.
